      <h2>Commercial Slushie Machine Maintenance</h2>
      <p>Maintaining a commercial slushie machine is essential to ensure it operates efficiently, produces high-quality
        beverages, and has a long operational life. Here are some key steps and tips for maintaining a commercial slushie
        machine:</p>
      <p><strong>Daily Maintenance</strong></p>
      <p>1. <strong>Cleaning the Exterior</strong>:</p>
      <p> - Wipe down the exterior of the machine with a damp cloth and mild detergent.</p>
      <p> - Avoid using abrasive cleaners or materials that can scratch the surface.</p>
      <p>2. <strong>Empty and Clean the Hopper</strong>:</p>
      <p> - Drain any remaining slushie mix at the end of the day.</p>
      <p> - Rinse the hopper with warm water to remove any residual mix.</p>
      <p> - Use a soft brush to scrub the interior, ensuring all sticky residues are removed.</p>
      <p>3. <strong>Sanitize</strong>:</p>
